subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Frons narrow at mid-length, narrower than width of anterior ocellus (
Figs 7
). Postpedicel 1.5 times length of scape and pedicel combined (
Fig. 8
). Scutum dark brown, with light brown region near postpronotal lobe (
Fig. 10
). Pleura orange-brown, except anepisternum and anterior half of katepisternum somewhat darker brown (
Fig. 9
). Wing veins M 
1
and M 
4
reaching wing margin (
Fig. 13
). Fore and mid tarsomere 1 pale yellow with dark apex (
Figs 5–6
). Hind tarsomeres 3–5 with short, blunt black spine-like ventral setae (
Figs 11–12
). Hypandrium narrow, oval about 2 times longer than wide, with 4 long setae near apex, arranged in trapezoidal pattern (
Fig. 14
).

